The paper deals with the design and analysis of a dynamic dictionary, which is a fundamental data structure in computer science. The paper focuses on the trade-off between update time, lookup time, and space consumption, which are all related to data structures and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the use of hashing and permutation-based techniques, which are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also presents a de-amortized perfect hashing scheme, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
